00:08:29.330 --> 00:08:34.040 position:56%
within our own analytical frameworks
and our own conceptual categories.

00:08:34.040 --> 00:08:37.400
Some of the central tenants of
the North Korean personality cult.

00:08:37.400 --> 00:08:40.710
This might seem to be
a strange thing to say

00:08:40.710 --> 00:08:44.260
that we're being influenced
by North Korean propaganda.

00:08:44.260 --> 00:08:47.860
Yet, nowhere is this more
clear than our own obsession

00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:49.590
with the Kim family, which in

00:08:49.590 --> 00:08:52.740
so many ways reproduces
the same obsession

00:08:52.740 --> 00:08:55.260
about leadership that's
coming out of Pomnyum.

00:08:55.260 --> 00:08:58.400
In our own histories just like
in North Korean histories,

00:08:58.400 --> 00:09:01.540
Kim LLsung remains virtually
the sole historical figure.

00:09:01.540 --> 00:09:05.310
The only agent of historical
action, decision and change.

00:09:05.310 --> 00:09:08.140
I'll give you one quick example
on how this works itself out.

00:09:08.140 --> 00:09:11.830
It's common for research on North
Korea to simply use a speech

00:09:11.830 --> 00:09:14.040 position:56%
of Kim LLsung as a historical source

00:09:14.040 --> 00:09:17.320
to account what happened
on a certain issue.

00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:20.290
Embedded in this type of
methodology is an assumption

00:09:20.290 --> 00:09:23.630
that because we believe North
Korea is a totalitarian country,

00:09:23.630 --> 00:09:27.480
there are no limits to the
personal rule of Kim LLsung.

00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:32.800 position:56%
What Kim says in any given speech
translates into action on the ground

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:35.980
with virtually no mediation.

00:09:35.980 --> 00:09:38.600
Now, when we think about the
twentieth century more globally,

00:09:38.600 --> 00:09:42.200
right, it's hard to imagine the
history of any other country

00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:47.560
where such a methodology just
quote the leader is acceptable

00:09:47.560 --> 00:09:48.860
or appropriate.

00:09:48.860 --> 00:09:50.900
When it comes to North
Korean history, however,

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:54.580
what Kim says goes, as far
as history is concerned.

00:09:54.580 --> 00:09:56.580
Moreover, there's no way out.

00:09:56.580 --> 00:09:57.880
It's a dead-end.

00:09:57.880 --> 00:10:00.580
We use high-level North
Korean propaganda, speeches,

00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:03.380
declarations of party
congresses, the editorials

00:10:03.380 --> 00:10:05.350
of the main newspaper,
legal statutes,

00:10:05.350 --> 00:10:08.730
TV news broadcast,
etcetera as our sources.

00:10:08.730 --> 00:10:12.110
All of which have the promotion
of the personality cult of one

00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:16.100 position:56%
of their priorities and that the key
assumption of Kim is at the center

00:10:16.100 --> 00:10:19.240
of all this action and this is what
we reproduce in our own studies.

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:22.440
There's a circularity in this,
and I think we can find it

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:24.340
in a website like this right.

00:10:24.340 --> 00:10:27.750
It's talking about Kim
Jong and looking at things.

00:10:27.750 --> 00:10:29.100
But what's not in the title is

00:10:29.100 --> 00:10:31.310
that we are looking
at the website, right.

00:10:31.310 --> 00:10:35.200
We're constantly looking at the
leadership for what they're up to.

00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:38.330
And a source like this
gives us no way of talking

00:10:38.330 --> 00:10:41.770
about anything but the leadership.

00:10:41.770 --> 00:10:46.300
So, just like Kim Jong and
looking at things, this website,

00:10:46.300 --> 00:10:49.020
we can laugh at the
way Kim is exalted.

00:10:49.020 --> 00:10:51.900
But we can't get outside
its bounds, right.

00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:55.450
The pictures are still of Kim,
and we keep looking at them.

00:10:55.450 --> 00:10:58.920
We roundly criticized the
personality cult and instead

00:10:58.920 --> 00:11:01.700
of calling him the great
leader we might think of him

00:11:01.700 --> 00:11:04.120
